cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the problem of delivering content cached in a wireless network, which involves information theory, networking, and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the performance of the wireless network, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The proposed communication scheme achieving the inner bound involves algorithms and optimization, which could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the common architecture of nearest-neighbor cache selection, which could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
